comment.body:
@caryoscelus: I think "notifications" on a site in a browser on desktop doesn't sound the same as in an app on a phone. Phones are in large part for being contacted and notified of things. Browsers are for going *to* places.
Imagine getting home from a restaurant and someone walking in asking if you want a drink refill. You expect that while you're "there" but not after.

Maybe I'm just old hat not wanting browsers and web tech to do literally everything all the time.
